cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.OS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a new programming model for concurrent access to objects in a shared memory system, which can be applied to distributed and parallel computing scenarios. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the consistency semantics of different data types and evaluates their performance and scalability. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a new programming model for concurrent access to shared objects. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems): The paper discusses the performance and scalability of different implementations for concurrent access to shared objects, which can be relevant for operating systems. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper evaluates the performance and scalability of different implementations for concurrent access to shared objects.
